benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/catalog/versions - Retrieve a list of catalog versions

covered: Valid Request: Global and tenant-scoped successful retrievals are covered (TC01, TC02, TC14) including content-type and ISO-8601 date validation.
Empty Response: Database-empty scenarios are covered (TC03, TC13) and verify empty JSON array with no stack traces.

Query Parameters & Validation: Extensive accountId handling is covered (valid, non-existent, invalid format, empty, leading/trailing spaces, mixed case) — TC02, TC04, TC05, TC16, TC17, TC18 — plus unsupported extra params ignored (TC09).
Authorization (authentication): Missing/invalid/expired token cases are covered (TC06, TC07) returning 401.
Error handling & resilience: Service unavailable, downstream timeouts and misconfiguration are exercised (TC08 -> 503, TC11 -> possible 504, TC19 -> 500).
Security: SQL injection attempt in accountId handled (TC12) and ensures no sensitive information exposure.
Performance / Load: Large dataset performance (10,000 items) and response-time expectation covered (TC10); concurrency / resource utilization covered (TC15).
Response format & accessibility: Content-type checks and machine-readable JSON verification (TC01, TC02, TC20) plus "no UI elements" assertion (TC20).
Malformed / unexpected responses: Tests cover malformed JSON producing server error (TC19) and verify appropriate error messaging.
Extra robustness checks: Regression test for previously fixed empty-array issue present (TC13).
gaps: Pagination: No tests verify pagination behavior (offset/limit/page, Link/X-Total-Count headers) or paginated responses for large datasets — TC10 does not assert pagination.
Caching behavior: No tests check caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control, Last-Modified) or conditional GET behavior (If-None-Match -> 304).
Rate limiting / throttling: No explicit tests to trigger/verify rate-limit responses (429) or Retry-After headers; TC15 concurrency checks performance but not throttling behavior.
Authorization (authorization/permissions): No tests for 403 Forbidden or role/tenant-scoped authorization failures (valid token but insufficient privileges / cross-tenant access).
Ordering / uniqueness: No assertions about ordering/stability of returned dates or deduplication of effective dates.
Method handling / content negotiation: No tests for invalid HTTP methods (expect 405) or Accept header negotiation (e.g., non-JSON Accept -> 406/handled response).

Boundary / extreme conditions: While TC10 covers 10k items, there are no tests for larger boundary conditions (e.g., very large payloads that may cause memory/timeout), chunking, or partial responses.
Headers & metadata: No checks for other useful response headers (Content-Length, pagination headers, caching-related headers).
recommendations: Add pagination tests: create > page-size items and verify pagination parameters (limit/offset or page/pageSize), Link and X-Total-Count headers, and behavior when requesting out-of-range pages.
Add caching tests: verify ETag and Cache-Control are present; perform conditional GETs with If-None-Match / If-Modified-Since and assert 304 Not Modified behavior.
Add rate-limiting tests: send bursts of requests to validate 429 responses and presence of Retry-After header; include graceful degradation behavior.
Add authorization/permissions tests: verify 403 responses for valid tokens lacking necessary tenant/scope permissions and ensure tenant isolation (no cross-tenant data leakage).
Add ordering/uniqueness tests: assert deterministic ordering of dates (if an order is required by spec) and verify duplicates are handled as expected (unique vs. duplicate entries).
Add method-negotiation tests: verify non-GET methods return 405 Method Not Allowed and unsupported Accept headers are handled (406 or fallback to JSON).
Expand boundary/performance tests: test larger-than-10k payloads, memory/timeouts, and streaming/chunked responses if applicable; include SLA assertions under load.
Verify response headers & metadata: assert Content-Length, appropriate caching headers, and any pagination-related headers are present and correct.
Add timezone/ISO variants tests: verify strictness of ISO-8601 parsing (timezone offsets, Z vs +00:00) and that returned strings are consistent and parseable by clients.
